## Project Summary

### Purpose

A launcher for pre-made Claude Code agents in isolated Docker containers. Each agent has distinct instructions, model, and parameters, but shares OAuth credentials and a persistent workspace. Solves the friction of re-authenticating and re-configuring Claude Code per persona.

### Tech Stack

- Python 3 (single-file launcher, ~100 lines)
- Docker + Docker Compose (per-agent containers)
- Debian Bookworm slim base image, Claude Code CLI installed via `claude.ai/install.sh`
- Python deps: `pick` (TUI picker), `python-dotenv` (parse `.conf` files)
- No tests, no CI, no lockfile

### Project Structure

```
/workspace/
  run.py                 # Entry point: picks agent, syncs state, runs docker compose
  Dockerfile             # Non-root claude user (matches HOST_UID), pre-creates memory dir
  docker-compose.yml     # One service: claude-code. Bind-mounts workspace + per-agent state
  README.md              # User-facing docs
  TODO.txt               # Open ideas (skills/context-dump command, tips from a YT video)
  .dockerignore          # Single '*' — build context is empty; nothing copied into image
  agents/                # Agent definitions (.md = CLAUDE.md; .conf = env overrides)
  custom_commands/       # Shared /slash commands mounted read-only into every agent
    write-summary.md     # This summary's prompt
  tips/                  # Plain-text notes (chat syntax, login, configuration gotchas)
```

**Agents** (each `<name>.md` becomes the agent's `CLAUDE.md`; `<name>.conf` is optional env override):

| Name | Role | Model | Effort | Notes |
|------|------|-------|--------|-------|
| `poet` | Dramatic literary commentator; quotes Shakespeare, Dante, Python, etc. | sonnet-4-6 | medium | Memory ON; 18K output tokens; keeps a "Quip Ledger" of user-loved lines |
| `researcher` | Doc-scouring researcher with source priority + Sources section | opus-4-7 | max | Thinking on; 40K out / 100K read; autocompact at 60% |
| `golem` | Fast, one-sentence simpleton for cheap ops | haiku-4-5 | low | Thinking/memory/crons/subagents all disabled |
| `strict-reviewer` | Severity-tagged code reviewer (🔴🟡🔵) | default | — | No `.conf` |
| `refactorer` | Perfectionist advisor; proposes, never imposes | default | — | No `.conf` |
| `dockerized-claude-code-improver` | Meta-agent to improve this repo itself | default | — | No `.conf` |

`agents/default.conf` = `claude-opus-4-7` + `CLAUDE_CODE_EFFORT_LEVEL=max` + thinking on. Used only when agent has no own `.conf`.

### Architecture

`run.py` is the whole control plane:

1. `select_agent()` (`run.py:25`) — globs `agents/*.md` (excluding `default`), shows `pick` menu labelled with each file's first heading.
2. `parse_conf()` (`run.py:42`) — loads `<name>.conf` if present, else falls back to `default.conf`. **Per-agent `.conf` fully replaces `default.conf` (not merged — agent configs must re-declare any defaults they still want).**
3. `sync_state()` (`run.py:50`) — ensures `~/.claude-agents/<name>/`, optionally wipes prior `history.jsonl`, copies the agent `.md` to `CLAUDE.md`, touches shared `.claude.json` / `.credentials.json` / workspace `.claude_summary`.
4. `ensure_image()` (`run.py:69`) — runs `docker compose build` unconditionally on every launch (cached, but adds a second or two).
5. `launch()` (`run.py:77`) — exports env vars, forwards `conf` keys via `-e KEY` flags, execs `docker compose run --rm -it claude-code` with any extra CLI args.

**Bind mounts** (`docker-compose.yml:11`):

- `${AI_WORKSPACE:-/ai_workspace}` → `/workspace` (shared project dir)
- `~/.claude-agents/<name>/` → `/home/claude/.claude` (per-agent state)
- `~/.claude-agents/.claude.json` → `/home/claude/.claude.json` (shared account)
- `~/.claude-agents/.credentials.json` → `/home/claude/.claude/.credentials.json` (shared OAuth)
- `./custom_commands` → `/home/claude/.claude/commands:ro` (shared slash commands)
- `${AI_WORKSPACE}/.claude_summary` → `/home/claude/.claude/projects/-workspace/memory/MEMORY.md` (this file; written in-container, persisted to host, auto-loaded by Claude Code's memory system)

### Conventions and Patterns

- Agent instructions are plain markdown; the first line is a heading used as the picker label.
- `.conf` files are dotenv-style and **exported as env vars wholesale**, so any key the CLI understands can be set there (see `default.conf` for a long annotated list of Claude Code env vars).
- The image runs as user `claude` with UID matching the host (`HOST_UID` build arg from `run.py:80`), so bind-mounted files stay host-writable.
- `.dockerignore` is `*` — the build context sends nothing; everything inside the image comes from apt + the installer script. Don't add `COPY` instructions expecting workspace files.
- Memory-mount parent `/home/claude/.claude/projects/-workspace/memory/` is pre-created in `Dockerfile:16` with `chown claude:claude` so the `MEMORY.md` bind mount lands on a claude-owned dir (Docker would otherwise root-own the auto-created parent).

